The course introduces students to the main problems and terms in ethics. Ethics and morality. Descriptive vs evaluative judgments. The origin of moral norms. Are values subjective or objective? Are moral standards universal or relative to culture? Responsibility. Moral motivation. Self-interest. The course also gives a brief overview of the main theories of ethics: ethics of virtue, utilitarianism, kantianism, contractualism.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) To give an overview of the main problems and concepts of ethics, 2) to develop skills of argumentation and debate, 3) to support personal values clarificationLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course the student: 
1)	Understands the meanings of the most relevant terms in ethics and is able to use them.
2)	Has overview of the main theories of ethics, is able to characterize them, knows their strengths and weaknesses and differentiates their forms.
